    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Income Ceiling Rises</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maximum earned income subject to Social Security taxes will rise 5.5 percent to $80,400 next year from $76,200 this year (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The maximum earned income subject to Social Security taxes will rise 5.5 percent next year, to $80,400 from $76,200 this year, according to the Social Security Administration.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The maximum earned income subject to Social Security taxes will rise 5.5 percent next year, to $80,400 from $76,200 this year, according to the Social Security Administration.</p>
        <p>The maximum tax paid directly by workers will increase to $4,984.80 from $4,724.40. Employers pay at the same rate as workers, and the self-employed pay both sides of the tax, but can deduct half of the tax on their income-tax returns.</p>
        <p>PERSONAL BUSINESS: DIARY</p>
      </block>
